      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ATMOSPHERIC ROCK (5) was impressive through the Wagga carnival but has been severely outclassed in town recently. This suits him much better coming back to country level and firmer footing is also a big tick. Drawn ideally down low for Guymer and he can bounce back with a bang. CRAVING MAGIC (3) has been sound this campaign without winning, but he's won 2/4 third-up in the past and now Brodie Loy hops on board. Can stroll forward from the draw and with his profile suggesting he's got another gear to find. Can get back to winning form. SUTTON VELLA (2) has gone back-to-back in Federals, winning 26 days ago by 0.4L. She's likely to be in the second half of the field again, but Cahill sticks with her and she can bring up the hat-trick. RAVALLI (4) steps up in trip now and the inside draw should see him much closer in the run. Can't be left out. WHO BUT ROO (1) is good enough to win this if he's up to his best.",
